275":"omkring 1275","about 1240":"omkring 1240","1218":"1218","Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Skotland","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Skotland","Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Inverness-shire, Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1230–17 February 1288":"1230–17 februari 1288","1230–1288":"1230–1288","1218–1298":"1218–1298","1240–1332":"1240–1332","1270–1297":"1270–1297","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1203–1280":"1203–1280","17 February 1288":"17 februari 1288","1275":"1275","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1332":"1332","1288":"1288","1298":"1298","about 1275":"circa 1275","about 1240":"circa 1240","1218":"1218","Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Schotland","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Schotland","Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Inverness-shire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1230–17 February 1288":"1230–17 February 1288","1230–1288":"1230–1288","1218–1298":"1218–1298","1240–1332":"1240–1332","1270–1297":"1270–1297","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1203–1280":"1203–1280","17 February 1288":"17 February 1288","1275":"1275","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1332":"1332","1288":"1288","1298":"1298","about 1275":"about 1275","about 1240":"about 1240","1218":"1218","Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Comyn","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English, Irish:  see  Cumming  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cumming","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): most probably a habitational name from Bosc-Benard-Commin in Eure, France. This place lies on the edge of the Forêt de Rouvray, near Rouen, in the heart of the district from which came numerous Domesday barons, and so is much more likely to be the source of the name than Comines in Nord. The name is also possibly derived from the personal name <i>Cumin</i>, which is found in Norfolk, Lincolnshire, and Yorkshire in the 12th and 13th centuries and may be of Breton origin, according to Reaney. Compare Old Breton <i>Cunmin</i>, which also appears as <i>Cumin</i>, and is from <i>con-</i> ‘hound’ with an uncertain second element, perhaps the <i>min</i> ‘edge’ which is found in other personal names.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cuimín</b> (or <b>Ó Cuimín</b>) ‘son (or ‘descendant’) of <i>Cuimín</i>’, a personal name formed from a diminutive of <i>cam</i> ‘crooked’. There was a 7th-century abbot of Iona named <i>Cumin</i>. In Scotland, this Irish surname became confused with the Norman name.","History: A notable bearer of the Norman surname is Wilhelmus Comyn, Bishop of Durham, who came north to Scotland with King David I in 1124 and was appointed Chancellor of Scotland. He established his nephew Richard in Tynedale and Roxburghshire, and Richard also rose to be Chancellor of Scotland. The Comyn or Cumming family gained the earldoms of Buchan and Menteith and rose to be the most powerful noble family in Scotland in the century before the rise of King Robert Bruce."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When de Comyn was born in 1230, in Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, her father, Sir John I - Ruadh - The Red Comyn Earl of Badenoch - Justiciar of Galloway, was 15 and her mother, Amabalia Angus, was 28. She married Sir Andrew de Moray Justiciar of Scotia, Lord of Petty. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died on 17 February 1288, in Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1230–17 February 1288":"1230–17. veebruar 1288","1230–1288":"1230–1288","1218–1298":"1218–1298","1240–1332":"1240–1332","1270–1297":"1270–1297","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1203–1280":"1203–1280","17 February 1288":"17. veebruar 1288","1275":"1275","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1332":"1332","1288":"1288","1298":"1298","about 1275":"umbes 1275","about 1240":"umbes 1240","1218":"1218","Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Bothwell, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Inverness-shire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1230–17 February 1288":"1230–17. helmikuuta 1288","1230–1288":"1230–1288","1218–1298":"1218–1298","1240–1332":"1240–1332","1270–1297":"1270–1297","1215–1275":"1215–1275","1203–1280":"1203–1280","17 February 1288":"17. helmikuuta 1288","1275":"1275","1297":"1297","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1332":"1332","1288":"1288","1298":"1298","about 1275":"noin 1275","about 1240":"noi